div.p:
Frequent Sailings from ALEXANDRIA to LIVERPOOL, also Regular Services
                            from LIVERPOOL to ALEXANDRIA and to ALGERIA, MALTA, LEVANT, BLACK SEA,
                            and other Mediterranean Ports.

Lieutenant G. Stewart, Coldstream Guards, having reported his arrival in Egypt
                    from England, is taken on the strength of the Egyptian Army from 26th Ootober,
                    1905, with the rank of Bimbashi. He bas been posted to the 15th Sudanese.
